# Paths

## Rules

### Path pattern

Only: `work/{team}/{space}/{ticket-id}/{project-name}/`

### Deliverable

One `README.md` per project folder plus `references/`, `scripts/`, and `assets/` only.

- Do not create other files (notes, drafts, separate doc files).
- Add new problems, topics, or findings to that README.
- Never create a new folder or new README for new problems or topics.

### Project folders (per work project)

Per project folder only:

- **`references/`** — Other docs; kebab-case filenames; link from README.
- **`scripts/`** — Executable code (e.g. runbooks, one-off scripts).
- **`assets/`** — Templates, icons, images; embed in README with `![](assets/filename.ext)`.
- No other folders or loose files.

### Folder names

Only the team, space, ticket-id, and project-name folder names listed in the tree below are allowed by default. If the system thinks new folders need to be created for work that are not in this tree, ask the user to name them; the system may suggest names.

### Unlisted levels

If a level is not listed, ask before creating the path.

## Editable section

Only the content below can be changed. In the Tree use the box-drawing style (├ │ └) as in the repo README.

